@node "Main" "CLIMaster"

                              @{b}CLIMaster@{ub}

              @{fg shine}The Directory Utility@{fg text} @{b}© Graham Maddox 1996@{ub}

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

CLIMaster  is  a  friendly,  intuitive and versatile directory utility which
has power matching others of many times its size.  It is perfect for use in
a low memory or low disk space environment.



                            @{" Overview     " link "oview" 0}     
                            @{" Requirements " link "requirements" 0}     
                            @{" Copyright    " link "licence" 0}   
                            @{" The Listers  " link "listers" 0}    
                            @{" Button Bank  " link "butbank" 0}    
                            @{" The Menus    " link "menus" 0}

@endnode

@node "oview" "Overview"


@{b}Overview@{ub}

The way CLIMaster works is similar to the tried and tested programs such as
Directory Opus or SID. There are two @{" lister " link "listers" 0} windows - a source and a
destination. These are not locked as such, each time a directory is changed
the active lister becomes the source, and the other the destination. Both
listers have an indicator which says whether that lister is source or
destination.

With some operations such as file copying or moving the lister indicators
will not change until an action button (Copy, Move etc.) in the button bank
is selected, although the source lister will always be the one that was last
clicked upon.

The principle of operation is that files or directories are highlighted in
one of the listers and a button selected from the @{" button bank " link "butbank" 0} to perform
an operation on the selected files.

External programs are called to operate on certain types of files, for
example if a Protracker module is double clicked on, a module player of your
choice is called upon to play it.

Most operations in CLIMaster only require a source. If a destination is
required, and one is not selected when you try to do the operation,
CLIMaster will tell you.

@endnode

@node "requirements" "Requirements"


@{b}Requirements@{ub}

    - CLIMaster will run on any Amiga equipped with the OS 3xx ROM,
      and any amount of memory.

    - Gui4Cli (© Dimitris C.  Keletsekis) must be present, anywhere on
      the boot disk. Must be version 2.2 or above.

    - The asl.library in LIBS:
@endnode

