@node "listers" "The Lister Windows"


@{b}The Listers@{ub}

Each lister has its own directory navigation buttons.

 @{b}String Gadget@{ub} - You can go directly to any device or directory by
                 typing the full path into the string gadget.

 @{b}S@{ub}    - Selects the listview as the current Source.

 @{b}VOL@{ub}  - Takes the lister to the Device list. All Devices, Volumes and
        Assigns currently mounted to the system are displayed.

 @{b}ROOT@{ub} - Moves back up to the Root directory.

 @{b}PAR@{ub}  - Moves up one level to the Parent directory.

 @{b}All@{ub}  - Selects All directories and files in the lister.

 @{b}None@{ub} - De-selects all selected directories and files in the lister.

 @{b}Refr@{ub} - Refreshes the lister's display and updates its contents.

@{b} Move »»»@{ub} - Moves the lister's display 10 characters to the left.

 @{b}««« Move@{ub} - Moves the lister's display 10 characters to the right.


The following two buttons are common to both listers.

 @{b}S=D@{ub}  - Copies the contents of the Source lister to the destination
        lister. The actual source and destination remain unchanged.

 @{b}<-->@{ub} - Swaps the contents of the source and destination listers. The
        actual source and destination remain unchanged.

@endnode

